{
	"info": {
		"name": "API Starter Pack Showcase",
		"description": "# API Starter Pack — Showcase\n\nProduction-ready backend API starter built with **Java 21** and **Spring Boot 3**.\n\nThis collection demonstrates a fully working authentication system with **JWT + Refresh Token Rotation**, user management, and health monitoring — all following **Clean Architecture** principles.\n\n---\n\n## How to Run\n\n1. Start the environment: `docker-compose up`\n2. Click **Run** to execute the full test flow automatically\n3. All tokens and IDs are managed — zero manual setup\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nController → UseCase → Repository → Database\n```\n\n| Layer | Responsibility |\n|---|---|\n| Controller | HTTP concerns, validation, DTOs |\n| UseCase | Business logic |\n| Repository | Persistence (Spring Data JPA) |\n\n## Security\n\n- **Access Token**: JWT, 15-minute expiry, signed with HMAC-SHA256\n- **Refresh Token**: opaque UUID, SHA-256 hashed in database, 7-day expiry\n- **Token Rotation**: each refresh invalidates the previous token\n- **Passwords**: BCrypt hashed, never stored in plain text\n\n## Modules\n\n| Module | Endpoints |\n|---|---|\n| Auth | `POST /auth/login` · `POST /auth/refresh` · `POST /auth/logout` |\n| User | `POST /users` · `GET /users/me` · `GET /users/{id}` |\n| Health | `GET /health` · `/actuator/health` · `/actuator/prometheus` |\n\n---\n\n> **This is a showcase version.** Full production deployment (AWS ECS, CI/CD, infrastructure-as-code) is available as a service.\n\n[GitHub Repository](https://github.com/tplucara/spring-boot-api-starter) · [Swagger UI](http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html)",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
